I basically stopped eating fast food when I moved to N.Y. 15 years ago. I was in Brooklyn, and there was no need with wonderful fresh food on every corner... But 6 months ago, my wife and I had twins boys. No more time for an elitist pallet... We spontaneously went to the McD's on grand street during our morning walk for a quick breakfast last week, and I'll tell ya what; they have stepped up their game. I was expecting nothing, and left pleasantly surprised. It is newly remodeled (tastefully I might add). The ordering kiosk interface was a little clunky, but we got through it easily even with my wife's custom order. The food came out fast, fresh, and far less greasy than I  remember. Bonus: there was  plenty of space, and no snarky judgement about our double wide stroller! I wont be back often, I'm 41 after all and can't eat like I'm 21, but I'll definitely be back.
